======================================================
04_03_matchup_summary.sql - DESCRIPTION
======================================================

Description:
This SQL script creates a final summary table that
analyzes head-to-head matchups between pairs of teams
across the entire dataset.

It builds on the detailed exploration from 03 by
combining all important matchup metrics into a single
structured output.

The goal is to understand:
- how often teams face each other
- which team dominates each matchup
- how frequently matches end in draws
- and how these matchups behave in terms of scoring,
  intensity, and overall match activity

------------------------------------------------------
Structure of the Script
------------------------------------------------------

The script is implemented as a single aggregated query.

It first normalizes team pairs so that each matchup is
represented consistently (Team A vs Team B = Team B vs Team A).

Then, it calculates:
- total matches per matchup
- wins for each team and number of draws
- win and draw percentages
- average goals and goal difference
- average disciplinary metrics (cards)
- average match activity metrics (offsides, corners,
  fouls, and shots)

------------------------------------------------------
CSV Output Description (matchup_summary.csv)
------------------------------------------------------

The output of this script is a compact table where each
row represents a unique pair of teams.

It includes:
- matchup frequency (total matches)
- head-to-head performance (wins and draw rates)
- scoring behavior (goals and competitiveness)
- match intensity (cards)
- match activity (offensive and defensive actions)

This file serves as the matchup-level analytical dataset
of the project and is designed for comparison,
visualization, and deeper analysis using Python or
other tools.